// Problem section — the "why" narrative
---

<section id="problem" class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-8">
    <h2 class="font-bold tracking-tight text-foggy-ink" style="font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px);">
      The cloud doesn't fit Africa.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-[17px] leading-[1.6] text-foggy-ink">
      <p>
        AWS, Azure, and Google charge a 10-50× markup over actual compute cost for managed AI services like transcription and embedding. That math works in San Francisco. It doesn't work in Nairobi.
      </p>

      <p>
        The closest hyperscaler region to most African capitals is 2,000 miles away. Data leaves the country to be processed. Latency is unpredictable. Sovereignty is impossible. And the languages most of Africa speaks — Swahili, Kinyarwanda, Amharic, Hausa — aren't well supported by services priced as if they were.
      </p>

      <p class="text-[22px] font-bold text-foggy-ink pt-4">
        Foggy fixes this by moving the inference itself onto hardware that's already in the building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
